The result of the foregoing comparisons between Servius and Macrobius is this: that in the great majority os cases where Servius and Macrobius have identioel notes, those of Macrobius are far the fuller, clearer, and more logical; that in the collections of parallel passages from Homer Macrobius has some which Servius has not, Servius many more which Macrobius has not, and there are many in common. Hence the natural inference is not (as Ribbeck thinks) that Macrobius was using a fuller form of the actual commentary of Servius than that which we now posseSS, but that both Macrobius and Servius were drawing upon older commentaries and criticisms,
